    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 3. The single below-level factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted with explicit scope restriction: the validated model is applicable only to the standard ASTM F1717 configuration tested. All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The credibility evidence package is accepted for submission to FDA in support of the 510(k) for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw system. Note: package conforms to ProfileMinimal; digital signature pending completion of institutional signature workflow and will be appended prior to final archival submission.",
